rComments: Was pretty good. textbook was cheap, but i'd recommend getting it as I think it would be more challenging if you don't have it. Was a fair grader, but make sure you participate in DGDs, otherwise you loose easy marks. I'd say she was an average grader, and the workload was fair

Doesn't care about her students or their sass accommodations. The work isn't difficult but I never felt any motivation for her class. Her lectures are recorded and asynchronous but you are marked for participation in the DGD. Her class and brightspace is unorganized, it is hard to find information. I would avoid her if possible.
